The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the government. Lisa Porter of Virginia has been nominated to be the Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering. Patrick J. Fuchs of Wisconsin and Michelle A. Schultz of Pennsylvania have been nominated to be Members of the Surface Transportation Board. James Edward Campos of Nevada has been nominated to be the Director of the Office of Minority Economic Impact in the Department of Energy. Peter C. Wright of Michigan has been nominated to be an Assistant Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency. Jon Parrish Peede of Mississippi has been nominated to be the Chairperson of the National Endowment for the Humanities. Michael J. Desmond of California has been nominated to be Chief Counsel for the Revenue Service and Assistant General Counsel in the Department of the Treasury.